INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States House of Representatives and the United States Senate to pass and for the President to sign into law S. 1773/ H.R. 3286, the Local Farms, Food and Jobs Act of 2011.
EventItemMatterName: The Local Farms, Food and Jobs Act of 2011. (S. 1773/ H.R. 3286)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Assembly to pass A.8846, the New York State Senate to pass companion bill S.6077, and the Governor to sign such legislation into law, which would require the New York State Department of Corrections and Community Supervision to place incarcerated adults in correctional facilities located in proximity to the primary place of residence of such individuals’ minor children.
EventItemMatterName: Place incarcerated adults in correctional facilities located in proximity to the primary place of residence of such individuals’ minor children. (S.6077 and 8846)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to require a plan for the phase-out of the use of typewriters in city government.
EventItemMatterName: Require a plan for the phase-out of the use of typewriters in city government.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation establishing the New York DREAM fund commission, which will advance the educational opportunities of children of immigrants through scholarship programs for higher education.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing the New York DREAM fund commission.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to reject the Birthright Citizenship Act of 2011, which would end the recognition of automatic birthright citizenship for certain classes of people who are born in this country to non-citizen parents.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to reject the Birthright Citizenship Act of 2011

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon New York City’s Board of Elections to promptly and fully comply with both the spirit and letter of the New York State Election Law by promoting the enfranchisement of New York City voters through the provision of Russian translations of voting materials.
EventItemMatterName: Promoting the enfranchisement of NYC voters through the provision of Russian translations of voting materials.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for civil discourse in presidential campaigns and debates, and condemning a candidate's statements claiming that children in poor neighborhoods lack work habits and have no one around them that work and referring to child labor laws as stupid.
EventItemMatterName: Civil discourse in presidential campaigns and debates, and condemning a candidate's statements claiming that children in poor neighborhoods lack work habits and have no one around them that work and referring to child labor laws as stupid.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of A.6369, which would amend the Penal Law by increasing the penalties for certain offenses committed against an elderly person who is 60 or older, and calling on the Senate to introduce and pass a companion bill, and on the Governor to sign such legislation.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the penalties for certain offenses committed against an elderly person who is 60 or older. (A.6369)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to parking violations issued for the failure to display a muni-meter receipt.
EventItemMatterName: Parking violations issued for the failure to display a muni-meter receipt.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring secondhand automobile dealers to furnish bonds to the city.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring secondhand automobile dealers to furnish bonds to the city.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring secondhand automobile dealers to keep electronic records of purchases and sales.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring secondhand automobile dealers to keep electronic records of purchases and sales.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting vending on the sidewalk abutting no standing zones adjacent to hospitals.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting vending on the sidewalk abutting no standing zones adjacent to hospitals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to extending the rent stabilization laws.
EventItemMatterName: Extending the rent stabilization laws.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the collection of waste and recyclables from not-for-profit corporations by the department of sanitation.
EventItemMatterName: Collection of waste and recyclables from not-for-profit corporations by the department of sanitation.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Water Board to set water and sewer rates to cover only the capital and operating expenses related to operating, maintaining, protecting, and improving the City’s drinking water and wastewater systems, and not to set these fees to pay money into the general fund of the city or for other functions undertaken by the Department of Environmental Protection not related to water and wastewater management.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Water Board to set water and sewer rates.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States House of Representatives to restore the Mass Transit Account that would be eliminated by the American Energy and Infrastructure Jobs Act of 2012 (H.R. 7), and calling upon the United States House of Representatives to support Congressman Jerrold Nadler’s bipartisan amendment to restore transit funding to H.R. 7, and calling on the United States Senate to not adopt H.R. 7 without such restoration.
EventItemMatterName: American Energy and Infrastructure Jobs Act of 2012 (H.R. 7)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Consumer Affairs to establish a uniform rating system for retail food stores.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Department of Consumer Affairs to establish a uniform rating system for retail food stores.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale and use of gas-powered leaf blowers.
EventItemMatterName: Sale and use of gas-powered leaf blowers.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Village Voice Media to stop accepting adult services advertisements on its online classified site, Backpage.com, because it serves as a platform to traffic minors and adult victims for sex.
EventItemMatterName: Village Voice Media to stop accepting adult services advertisements on its online classified site, Backpage.com

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to doubling the civil penalty for illegally operating a motorized scooter.
EventItemMatterName: Doubling the civil penalty for illegally operating a motorized scooter.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Metropolitan Transit Authority to investigate how the New York City Police Department is enforcing section 1050.7(j) of the MTA Rules of Conduct, regarding disorderly conduct in the subway.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to investigate how the NYPD is enforcing section 1050.7(j) of the MTA Rules of Conduct, regarding disorderly conduct in the subway.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to phase out and eliminate the use of polystyrene food trays within two years through the use of biodegradable food trays or biodegradable food containers instead.
EventItemMatterName: Dep't of Education to phase out and eliminate the use of polystyrene food trays within two years through the use of biodegradable food trays or biodegradable food containers instead.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution recognizing September as Suicide Awareness Month in New York City and calling upon government agencies and non-governmental organizations to focus on teen suicide prevention.
EventItemMatterName: Recognizing September as Suicide Awareness Month in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution determining that a public emergency requiring rent control in the City of New York continues to exist and will continue to exist on and after April 1, 2012.
EventItemMatterName: Determining that a public emergency requiring rent control in the City of NY continues to exist and will continue to exist on and after April 1, 2012.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass, and the President to sign into law, the “Restore the American Dream for the 99% Act” to support job creation, increase revenue and savings and protect critical services.
EventItemMatterName: Restore the American Dream for the 99% Act

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign the Internet System for Tracking Over-Prescribing Act (A.8320/S.5720A), legislation that would create an online database to report and track the prescription and dispensing of certain controlled substances.
EventItemMatterName: Internet System for Tracking Over-Prescribing Act (A.8320/S.5720A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of tax liens.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of tax liens.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring a sign at inaccessible building entrances, public toilets, and elevators giving directions to the nearest available accessible entrance or facility for persons with disabilities when such  entrance or facility exists.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring a sign at inaccessible building entrances, public toilets, and elevators giving directions to the nearest available accessible entrance or facility for persons with disabilities.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Department of Labor to eliminate all banking fees on Direct Payment Cards used for unemployment insurance benefit payments.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Dept of Labor to eliminate all banking fees on Direct Payment Cards used for unemployment insurance benefit payments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to introduce and enact, and the Governor to sign, legislation that would amend the New York State Penal Law to define advancing or profiting from prostitution of an individual less than the age of sixteen as sex trafficking.
EventItemMatterName: Define advancing or profiting from prostitution of an individual less than the age of sixteen as sex trafficking.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York and the New York City Charter, in relation to the disciplinary decisions made by the Commissioner of the New York City Police Department.
EventItemMatterName: Disciplinary decisions made by the Commissioner of the NYPD.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting bias-based profiling.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting bias-based profiling.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring law enforcement officers to provide notice and obtain proof of consent to search individuals.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring law enforcement officers to provide notice and obtain proof of consent to search individuals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to requiring law enforcement officers to identify themselves to the public.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Senate to pass and the Governor to sign S.3921, which would amend the New York State Executive Law in relation to the duties of state police when an offense is committed by a police officer resulting in serious physical injury to another person.
EventItemMatterName: Duties of state police when an offense is committed by a police officer resulting in serious physical injury to another person. (S.3921)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Assembly to pass A.4382, the New York State Senate to introduce and pass similar legislation, and the Governor to sign such legislation into law, granting the New York State Attorney General jurisdiction to investigate and prosecute police misconduct upon the request of the Governor or the District Attorney of the county wherein such misconduct was committed.
EventItemMatterName: Investigate and prosecute police misconduct upon the request of the Governor or the District Attorney of the county wherein such misconduct was committed. (A.4382)
